<br>
doesnt seem to be written in the script and I figure verant wouldnt want everyone to know what piece was on what mob anyways, kinda defeats the whole point dont you think?<br>
<br>
have fun in poh :)<br>
<br>
GeroSloth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxashrenthelost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xashren the Lost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 5:15:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/16/3550416.jpg height=168 width=200?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Visible Harmony armor?</span><hr size=1> <B><I>for obvious reasons mobs dont show armor they have in loot tables</B></I><br>
<br>
Untrue.<br>
<br>
Go to HighKeep and fight the goblins. With certain video cards, you can see a golden tint on their flesh, which indicates what piece of bronze is going to drop. Works for me, and several other people I've spoken to, but not sure if it works for everyone.<br>
